    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2891269019" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2891269019" />
    <a title="Wendy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51271722-wendy"><img alt="Wendy" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2891269019?book_show_action=true">Jul 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Wendy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Wendy" href="/user/show/51271722-wendy">Wendy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780451526250" href="/book/show/764269.The_Underdogs">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2891269019" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6713090170334917331">&quot;Revolutions begin fighting tyranny and end fighting themselves.&quot;-Saint-Just<br/><br/>With a Foreword by the incomparable Carlos Fuentes, I was looking forward to reading this novel written in the midst of the Mexican Revolution by Mariano Azuela. Unfortunately, I found it difficult to connect to the narrative and this halting, flawed prose. I think that is most likely due to the clunky and jarring translation by Sergio Waisman and I should probably read this groundbreaking novel in its original Spanish s</span>
  <span id="freeText6713090170334917331" style="display:none">"Revolutions begin fighting tyranny and end fighting themselves."-Saint-Just<br /><br />With a Foreword by the incomparable Carlos Fuentes, I was looking forward to reading this novel written in the midst of the Mexican Revolution by Mariano Azuela. Unfortunately, I found it difficult to connect to the narrative and this halting, flawed prose. I think that is most likely due to the clunky and jarring translation by Sergio Waisman and I should probably read this groundbreaking novel in its original Spanish so that I may experience what Fuentes was talking about this book. The translation was so irritatingly intrusive I could barely manage not to scream. If I saw a sentence with "ya" in it one more time, I felt I was going to throw the book through the window. "How are ya?" "I want ya to round up the men." STOP IT. Then, Waisman chose to take certain Spanish nicknames and translate them into English which simply did NOT work. "Quail", "Lard" and "Towhead." No, just NO.<br /><br />His cynicism and disillusionment with revolution were a welcome canvas on which the novel was drawn. The inevitable brutality, sociopathy, disillusionment, death, and men doomed to repeat failures over and over, for what?<br /><br />"I imagined a flowering prairie at the end of the road...and instead found myself in a swamp. My friend: there are events and men out here who are nothing but pure bile. And that bile drips on one's soul one drop at a time, until everything becomes soured, poisoned. Enthusiasm, dreams, ideals, joy...nothing! Before long none of that is left. Either one turns into a bandit just like them, or one disappears from the scene, hiding behind the walls of an impenetrable and fierce selfishness."<br /><br />There is no better description of war.<br /><br />Some brilliance here, but clouded by a heavy-handed translation.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6713090170334917331" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

