<div id="review_2686136633" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2686136633" />
    <a title="Clara McCollam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/76277608-clara-mccollam"><img alt="Clara McCollam" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2686136633?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Clara McCollam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Clara McCollam" href="/user/show/76277608-clara-mccollam">Clara McCollam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2686136633" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1481119768949582878"> Los de abajo <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/961341.Los_de_abajo' title='Los de abajo by Mariano Azuela' rel='nofollow noopener'>Los de abajo</a> is a novel by Mariano Azuela set during the Mexican Revolution. Although I don’t normally reach for novels set during military revolutionary times, this novel was more interesting than others in the sense that it has a complex web of characters that are all well developed and are constantly adding something to the story line. I think Azuela uses these characters very strategically to paint a full picture of the large gap between the rich and poor so the reader can bett</span>
  <span id="freeText1481119768949582878" style="display:none"> Los de abajo <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/961341.Los_de_abajo" title="Los de abajo by Mariano Azuela" rel="nofollow noopener">Los de abajo</a> is a novel by Mariano Azuela set during the Mexican Revolution. Although I don’t normally reach for novels set during military revolutionary times, this novel was more interesting than others in the sense that it has a complex web of characters that are all well developed and are constantly adding something to the story line. I think Azuela uses these characters very strategically to paint a full picture of the large gap between the rich and poor so the reader can better understand the significance and gravity of the discrepancies in the Mexican society during the Revolution. Being the first novel I have read about the Mexican Revolution, this novel opened my eyes to a whole new side of the reality at hand. Up until this point, we have developed an idea of what the Revolution was like through class discussions, but this novel took my visualization of the time period to the next level. The violence, the terror, the constant sense of fear resonating among “los de abajo”- all things that motivate them to continue their fight. Overall, this book was relatively challenging (especially with a lot of new Spanish vocabulary), but it gave me a very good look into this time period, almost like I was there myself alongside “los de abajo”.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1481119768949582878" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


