    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2686070423" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2686070423" />
    <a title="Miller Townes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/92216878-miller-townes"><img alt="Miller Townes" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2686070423?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Miller Townes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Miller Townes" href="/user/show/92216878-miller-townes">Miller Townes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2686070423" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17554569988867664801">Professor Barnett / Miller Townes / Washington and Lee University <br/><br/>I really enjoyed reading Los de abajo by Mariano Azuela. As someone who&apos;s first language is English, not Spanish, I felt that a lot of the vocabulary was very colloquial and found myself looking up many words in the dictionary. This made if fairly difficult to read but I still enjoyed the content. I liked the vivid descriptions of the scenery and felt that they made an impact on the interpretation of the events occurring in the bo</span>
  <span id="freeText17554569988867664801" style="display:none">Professor Barnett / Miller Townes / Washington and Lee University <br /><br />I really enjoyed reading Los de abajo by Mariano Azuela. As someone who's first language is English, not Spanish, I felt that a lot of the vocabulary was very colloquial and found myself looking up many words in the dictionary. This made if fairly difficult to read but I still enjoyed the content. I liked the vivid descriptions of the scenery and felt that they made an impact on the interpretation of the events occurring in the book. For example, some of the very graphic and vivid descriptions of the poverty in which the rebels lived and fought illustrated their difficult lower position to "los federales" in the conflict. Also the book serves to show that many Mexicans did not intentionally participate in the revolution but were instead dragged into this movement against their own will. Overall I gave this book four out of five stars because I think it is an important piece to read to understand the first several years of the revolution which are crucial to understanding Mexican society today. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17554569988867664801" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

